
======================================================================
DLE-001 Curl pipe to shell [CRITICAL]
======================================================================

Category:
  Command Injection  (detector: rules)

Description:
  Downloading and executing remote scripts is extremely dangerous.
  Used in 2018 xeactor attack.

Recommendation:
  Download scripts first, review them, then execute

CWE: CWE-94

Real-World Context:
  Used in the July 2018 'xeactor' attack where orphaned AUR packages
  (acroread, balz, minergate) were taken over and modified to
  download malicious scripts from ptpb.pw using curl.

Detection Patterns:
  - curl\s+[^|]+\|\s*(ba)?sh
  - curl .* \| sh
  - curl .* \| bash

Related Codes:
  DLE-002, DLE-003, PASTE-001

======================================================================
